'''Eddard Stark''', also known by his friends and family as '''Ned''', is a major character in the [[Season 1|first season]]. He is played by starring cast member [[Sean Bean]], and debuts in the [[Winter is Coming|series premiere]].

Eddard is the head of [[House Stark]] and [[Lord Paramount of the North]]. He is a dedicated husband and father, a loyal friend and an honorable lord. Eddard becomes [[Hand of the King]] to his lifelong friend, [[Robert Baratheon]], when the previous hand dies in suspicious circumstances. He follows his predecessor's footsteps and uncovers an incestuous relationship between Queen, [[Cersei Lannister]], and her brother, Ser [[Jaime Lannister]]. Robert dies after being injured while hunting and Eddard challenges the legitimacy of his successor, [[Joffrey Baratheon]], butÂ is betrayed by his political allies and arrested for [[treason]]. He confesses to the crime to protect his family, but is nevertheless [[Execution of Eddard Stark|executed]] due to Joffrey's impulsiveÂ sadism. The conflict between House Stark and [[House Lannister]] sets the stage for the [[War of the Four Kings|War of the Five Kings]].

